Agreement.

"Recipient" means anyone who receives the Program under this Agreement
or any Secondary License (as applicable), including Contributors.

"Derivative Works" means any work, whether in Source Code or other form,
that is based on (or derived from) the Program and for which the
editorial revisions, additions, or deletions represent, as a whole, an
original work of authorship.

"Modified Works" means any work in Source Code or other form that
results from an addition to, omission from, or other modification of
the contents of the Program, provided that such changes and/or additions
to the Program originate from and are Distributed by that particular
Contributor. A Modified Work is considered to be Distributed even if the
Modified Work is not yet Distributed.

"Distribute" means the acts of a) distributing or b) making available
in any manner that enables the transfer of a copy.

"Source Code" means the form of a Program preferred for making
